---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "microcontrollers — ecute.club";
---
<BaseLayout {title}>
  <article class="container">
    <h1>microcontrollers</h1>
    <p>a <strong>microcontroller (MCU)</strong> is a tiny computer-on-a-chip: CPU + flash + RAM + pins. boards like Arduino and ESP32 make them friendly.</p>

    <h2>what can they do?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>GPIO:</strong> read buttons, light LEDs.</li>
      <li><strong>PWM:</strong> dim LEDs, control motors.</li>
      <li><strong>ADC:</strong> read analog voltages (sensors).</li>
      <li><strong>serial buses:</strong> UART, I²C, SPI to talk to other chips.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>voltage &amp; limits</h2>
    <p>many modern MCUs are <strong>3.3 V</strong> logic; classic Arduino UNO is <strong>5 V</strong>. a single pin only sources/sinks small current (≈<em>tens</em> of mA). use a transistor/driver for motors/strips.</p>

    <h2>pwm &amp; adc (visual)</h2>
    <div class="diagram" role="img" aria-label="PWM square wave and ADC reading">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 560 130" width="100%" height="auto">
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="560" height="130" rx="16" fill="var(--card)"/>
        <text x="36" y="34" class="mono">pwm</text>
        <polyline points="80,80 120,80 120,40 180,40 180,80 240,80 240,40 300,40 300,80 340,80" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="360" y="34" class="mono">adc</text>
        <rect x="400" y="40" width="18" height="60" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <rect x="424" y="56" width="18" height="44" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <rect x="448" y="48" width="18" height="52" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <rect x="472" y="64" width="18" height="36" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <h2>nice first steps</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>blink an LED with PWM, then read a potentiometer via ADC to set brightness.</li>
      <li>use internal pull-ups for buttons: <code>pinMode(pin, INPUT_PULLUP)</code>; wire button to ground.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
